Blocks.childText: FREEDOM'S JUBILEE. Concluded. 17 men and fathers hoary, Raise your voi - ces loud and high! WINDHAM. L. M. READ. Mournful. Broad is the road that leads to death, And thousands walk to - gether there But wisdom shows a narrow path, With here and there a trav - el - ler. One thing needful. L. M. I. W HY will ye waste on trifling cares That life which God's compassion spares; While, in the various range of thought, The one thing needful is forgot? 2. Shall God invite you from above? Shall Jesus urge his dying love? Shall troubled conscience give you pain ? And all these pleas unite in vain? 3. Not SO your eyes will always view Those objects which you now pursue: Not so will heaven and hell appear When death's decisive hour is near. 4. Almighty God! Thy power impart; Fix deep conviction on each heart; Nor let us waste on trifling cares That life which thy compassion spares.
